<TITLE> Dhaka stocks fall in midday trade </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, August 6 (bdnews24.com)  Dhaka stocks fell in midday trade Monday, spurred by a sell-off in the bank, power and pharmaceuticals sector shares. The market shed almost 40 points in the morning trade. It regained after an hour on fresh buying but still remained in the negative terrain. The DGEN or general index slumped 18.91 points or 0.80 percent to reach 2334.45 at 11:55am. The DSI or all-share 17.96 points or 0.93 percent to 1906.74. Turnover clocked Tk 643.36 million after Sunday's close at Tk 1.56 billion. Of the issues traded, 44 gained, 105 added and 16 held steady. Square Pharma, BRAC Bank and Summit Power dominated the turnover board at 11:54 am. UCBL and DESCO were next to Summit Power. Square Pharma dropped to Tk 5211 from Tk 5254.75. BRAC Bank fell to Tk 947 from Tk 952.75. Summit Power remained almost flat at Tk 1301 against Tk 1301.75. UCBL rose to Tk 3569 from Tk 3535.5 on announcement that it would hold its pending AGMs for the five years from 1998 to 2002. DESCO traded lower at Tk 938 from Tk 960. National Bank, Southeast Bank, AB Bank, Power Grid Company of Bangladesh and Pubali Bank declined in turnover. bd
